review_text: Lots of convenient, covered parking. The spacious layout and thoughtful floor design make for a pleasant shopping experience. Floor staff were excellent. Went for waterproof shoes and bought the Mark s brand windriver boots which fit incredibly well. Walked 4K in the rain next day and didn t think about my feet once. Dog-friendly, too!
The girl with short hair and glasses at the front registers was really nice and helpful. Exchange process was smooth and i was done and out in less than 10 mins :)

Marks, it s like the Canadian tire of Canadian clothing and work gear.  Huge selection of safety gear and boots. Casual clothing etc.  online shopping is even better with easy store returns possible.  Lots of covered parking at this location.
You find clothes for everything and good brands

reviewer_name: R an A Ac an Ar
review_text: THE BOOTS DONT LAST THE WORK I PUT THEM THROUGH SO THE GREAT STAFFERS AT MARKS REIMBURSED ME SO MY WINTER WILL MEET ITS MATCH THANK YOU STAFFERS OF MARKS MY FEET APRECIATE YOU VERY VERY VERY MUCH LOVE YOU ALLLLL THANK YOU SO VERY VERY VERY MUCH XO:)
Amazing help from the Store Manager .. Jeremy thanks for your help .. New Dakotas for new Job.. Bless

Selenah really kind i cannot express how nice she is helping me througout my shopping experience. She helped me from the entrance until i found a specific pants that i need to work. she is super nice. I feel so lucky to start my day seeing her i love her vibes too.
It is convenient to park here and go shopping, the store is organized and staff are friendly to help me look for what I want.

I receive boot vouchers from my company annually and have always had issues using it at other branches because they didnt know how to process it and rather made me look like a Kyle. This store knew what it was and processed it promptly.  Ill stick to this store every new year.
Jessie is an amazing employee. Great customer service! Very patient and helpful. Head Office - replenish your stocks, do a better job!
Clean store, always helpful & plenty of parking

The staff was excellent. The manager was very accommodating. I returned items that I actually used ....socks and boots....they were both defective and there were no issues on them giving me a full refund...just make sure you keep your receipts.... Great customer service. 100 day guarantee on boots...make sure you remember that and keep the receipt...when you purchase a pair even when youve worn them.... because the rubber boots actually leaked after one month of use...theyll give you a refund or return it for another pair...:) thats great....

I walked out of this store much taller than when I went in. It was a refreshing and uplifting experience.  Even if you dont get the high quality work boots like I did at 30% off, you will feel absolutely buoyant when departing.  Only thing I might suggest is provide a courtesy chunky chocolate cookie upon checkout.
Had an item the wrong size and called around. Selena at this store was the most helpful. She was brilliant and patient on the phone, and made ran all over the store helping me track down items.

Came in today looking for womens winter and rain clothes. The amazing ladies at the front, valorie and loveleen were amazing and so helpful and kind. The customer service was unbelievable and very appreciated!! The absolute very best to you two ladies in the future!!

Ive passed by this place quite a few times over the years while shopping next door at Canadian Tire. The first time i went here on a monday afternoon to purchase a rain jacket for my 80 year old father. The older gentleman in the back was very helpful, I ended up purchasing two other items based on his recommendation.
Very Nice! I seem to buy all my clothes there. Good deals,
My favorite store for cargo pants and Construccion gear.
Clean and well stocked very nice
My family has been going to this location for almost 10years. Store is clean and has good selection for all kinds of work gear. Staff are helpful and friendly.

I come here for a specific article of clothing I have chosen beforehand. I exchange pleasantries with the cashier, politely decline help from the floor-associate. I try on a silly looking hat or two (pre-covid) and proceed to the cashier. These monthly excursions usually take no longer than 5 minutes. Overall, a very pleasant experience.
I got a great discount on the Keen carbon toe booths, thanks Marks for taking care the construction workers safety needs. Discounts is such a big help for us.

This is the best Marks location in the city (believe me, Ive been to all of them), plus its also the newest building and they have the most selection. Being next to Canadian Tire makes it a plus as you can get most of your hardware needs in one trip
I reserved a pair of steel toe shoes but they pick the wrong one for me at first but Salena is extremely nice and helpful to find me the correct one.

Superior customer service and a friendly staff. I have found exactly what I was looking for, thanks to Loveleens help. I highly recommend shopping there as they have competitive prices and a decent variety!
One of my go to stores, always has a great selection to choose from!
Great place for work clothes and just clothes that wear well. Staff were very helpful finding work boots for my husband. Great selection for men and women.
Very friendly staff and a shout out to Jacob who handled my transaction very efficiently and pleasantly. Store is organized and had everything I needed. Cheers!
Yeah the best quality clothes you can get.
I was greeted right away when I entered the store by Anna Maria and she was amazing,very patient and very knowledgeable about anything I asked her. I will go back to that Marks just because of her.

Only marks I like going to. The staff is amazing!!!!! Jasleen and Ethen have been extremely helpful over my last few visits. They understand my needs and go above and beyond. Extremely impressed and pleased. Thank you!!

Big Shout out to Jacob for putting the winter boots away for me !!! I had called on a busy Friday night and he was great !!! Excellent Customer Service Jacob !!! Thank You very much , the best Winter Boots I have had in a long time
Friendly and helpful staff. Bought a pair of Terra work boots, slip on ones, great pair of boots, comfortable and lightweight with steel stoe.
Great deals on clearance stuff, and gave me my IATSE discount even on clearance stuff.
I had questions about waterproofing my boots. One of the salesstaff used to work in construction and really knew his stuff. Gave me great suggestions.
Outstanding customer service and attention to customer needs. They carry a lot of inventory and sizes to meet all demand. Location highly recommended.

reviewer_name: A S C X N S I O N
review_text: Big location with huge selection of footwear and casual clothing, staff is very helpful with good attitudes. Definitely will shop here again.
Boxing Day SALE is the day to get all your work gear
If you are looking for Mark, you wont find him here. You will find a Marks work wearhouse with all the usual stuff. If thats not what your looking for then I dont know what else to say...
Great store and the people that work at that location are totally awesome.
Huge selection of clothing and footwear. Sale prices are great !
Lots of choices. Staff helped me a lot. Always good value.
Awesome sales today... Great selection to choose from... If you are looking for boots they are all on sale...
Thank you Leah and David for some awesome customer service! Its times like this during covid where quality service from a retailer makes a difference!
Sebastian took really good care of me today. I had a very positive experience at this location.
Good prices and brands with different price ranges. This particular location was not crowded at all, which was great
I just received some phenomenal service by Anna. Super helpful and genuinely cares about what gear will suit you best.
Quality, beauty, durable and nice designs for mens and womens clothing. Excellent customer service.
Great prices, good selection, helpful n friendly staff
lots of parking , helpful staff , not many though on shift , nice to go during big sales
This place it great a bit pricey but the quality u get is good and there close too love it
I bought an steel toe sneekers for my work with the timberland brand on it. They are prety light and comfort.
Can get Canadian Tire credits. Hiking shoes, safe shoes and t shirts
Friendly and helpful staff. Clean and organized inside. Good deals!
great staff, very helpful and patient, had exactly what i needed for my new job
The best for work clothes and the staff is really friendly/helpful.
Jeremy, the cashier who helped us was very pleasant and friendly!
The staff, however limited, was very helpful and they had exactly what I was looking for.
Grandview Marks one of the best Marks store to shop everything is organised and helpful employees
Excellent place for winter boots -- anything winter -- especially for cold northern Canadian climates.
20% off this and next weekend. Good sales great customer service
Boots are AWSOME QUALITY EXACTLY WHAT WE WERE LOOKING FOR! STAFF WAS GREAT!!
WoW great; I bought my tshirt with high quality
Picked up a pair of steel shoes, well designed a little light weighted.
Excellent goods, very good service.
Nice people work here, and the store is clean :)
Tony was awesome
Friendly and helpful Staff . Help find what I needed.
Very good quality clothes and shoes. Either for work or sports.
Marky Mark and the Working Bunch has some pretty good sales from time to time
Great staff..very helpful..great prices
Good if looking for work shoes or winter ones
Nice and friendly people work there
Great location free parking friendly staff
Great place for work related clothing!
Got what I needed and staff went out of their way to help me.
Ethan was very helpful.  Great service
Great service, super friendly staff!

The girl is very helping me! And also i call back to make sure my jean cutting length is maximum 3inch, not more than 3 inch, and the guy in the store was helping to pinch the length, i don t know both name, but they are friendly and very helpful! Happy of my purchase in the store first time, good experience!

I visited this store recently to find my size having been recommended by a friend. The staff were friendly and helpful. It was such a pleasant experience, one that rarely happens now when everything is online. I went in looking for one jumpsuit and now want multiple items! I usually have to get all my pants altered and today was the first day I found pants and jeans that fit perfectly. Excited to style and wear Duer when my purchases arrive.

Had a great experience my first time in Duer. Purchased the Fireside Girlfriend Black Jeans, Fleece-lined. Ania/Ana and Skyler were SO helpful, especially with advice on sizing. I was hesitant to buy a size smaller but they recommended it due to the expected stretch within a week of wear, and they were right! Thank you for your patience and kind advice!
The best pants I ever did buy! So comfy and they look just like original denim, but do not feel like denim! Get some! Youll love them

Great pants! I ve been buying Duer jeans and pants for more than 5 years. I love the quality and that it s a local company.  Had great service today from Skylar who was super helpful and turned around my opinion on the customer service here (it had previously been subpar service shopping in store).

This company has just taken my experience of buying jeans to a whole new level! I absolutely love their personal shopping schedule they ve implemented and their selection of cuts and colours is great. After being stuck at home for so long, getting to swing in their store, and climb the ladder wall, and shoot some hoops was an incredible bonus!

Can t buy any other pant. They are super comfortable, keep their shape and are throw in the washer/dryer. I have bought 2 pair jeans, pants for partner and son, 2 pair shorts & all are worn regularly and have been appreciated as gifts  what a find!
The staff there are all very friendly and helpful. They were able to help me find size and fits that work with my body type. I appreciate their help and welcoming attitude. Will definitely come back.

Great store and exceptional customer service! I bought my first pair of pants from DUER in October and haven t looked back  I just got another pair! A lovely retail associate by the name of Siobhan helped me find a pair, grabbed me sizes when I needed to size down, and had amazing product knowledge! I don t know what role they operate in at DUER, but man do they need a promotion! Thank you DUER team for a consistently great experience and AMAZING products!
The service I got from the Vancouver store was fantastic. And the online response to a question I had was great as well. Damn comfortable pants!!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Kevin, so glad your experience with us has been a positive one, and love to hear that youre a fan of our pants too. We appreciate you taking the time  to share with us and hope to welcome you back to the store one day!

review_text: Best pants ever! I came from out of town to try on the denim jumpsuit. Although they didnt have my size, the staff were so friendly and helpful without being pushy. They shared a link to my email if I chose to order my size online. I have since ordered and recieved the jumpsuit and its amazing! Excellent quality & fit. DUER you guys are awesome.

Had an issue with a tee shirt I bought from Duer. Brought it in and received exceptional service from Elorie (sp). She went above and beyond and was able to help me navigate the issue. Looking forward to stopping by the store again in the near future!

Ive been wearing DUER for a since about 2016 and I really appreciate the way they stand behind their product.  When some new jeans in a different cut just werent working out for me, the online CSR and the store manager on 4th Ave in Vancouver helped me out.  The manager found me better jeans and I was able to return the others. She was really interested in making sure I was happy with my DUERs. Will definitely be buying more of their jeans in the future.

Best pants you ll ever own! I had a great experience at DUER Vancouver. The customer service was top notch! I came in looking to find some pants and their manager, Angel, was super helpful in finding the perfect fit for me. They even offer to hem pants for you! Their pants are super comfortable and I find myself reaching for them everyday for whatever adventure I have planned for the day. I ll be coming back!
Every item Ive purchased from Duer has been top notch. Slowly replacing my wardrobe with Duer kit.

Stopped by the Duer store today after seeing their website. I like the clothing they have to offer and heard some good things about the quality and the fit. I was greeted by an associate when I walked in and service was good. The quality is good and I found the fit comfortable for myself. I like that the company is a Vancouver based company and will definitely be looking at some of their other clothing.

I ve had a great experience buying from DU/ER. Design is perfect. It fits your body perfectly and its super comfy to wear all day long. On top of the quality I would like to say the customer service experience is top-notch. I had a small issue on my first purchase, and they offered me to exchange it for free. This is exactly what you re expecting from a Canadian brand. Well done guys!

I love the joggers and fleece lined jeans and am now on my 2nd pair of Duer regular jeans - most comfy things ever. Staff are knowledgeable and not pushy. Also enjoying the Sunday morning yoga hosted by Duer at the store. Thanks for that free zen!
I love going to this store. The manager Angel is very kind and super helpful. She did a return for me yesterday right before they closed and was so accommodating. She definitely deserves the 5 stars
Jeans were there perfect fit, and the shipping process went smooth and efficiently.
Amazing customer service! Karleigh in customer support was incredibly helpful when I made a mistake on my order.
Incredible staff! Very friendly and inviting. Great experience

Best jeans shopping experience Ive ever had! My partner and I usually hate shopping for pants but this was actually enjoyable. The staff member who helped us was incredible and made us feel completely at ease. Unfortunately we didnt get her name, but she was working in the afternoon on Saturday June 11th at the flagship store on 4th and she was the best clothing salesperson Ive ever met. I really appreciated that our salesperson offered for us to try on both womens and mens pants, and that she didnt make assumptions about what pants style we might want to wear based on our gender. Also the atmosphere in the store is so relaxing I wanted to just hang out there all day. I would highly recommend Duer and will definitely be back!
My visit to Duer was the best Great atmosphere but most importantly the people working there Thank you for being kind Much appreciated! Anne

I went in and bought a pair of jeans. They were there to coach me all along the fitting process to help me find the right pair of jeans. The pair I got were initially a good fit but on my second wear I noticed the waist had significantly stretched out. I brought them back to show what had happened and they were happy to make an exchange. I now have a pair that is significantly better fitting. They also hemmed the new pair, which I was thankful for. The pants are great, so is the customer experience.

I was introduced to Du/er by a friend. It s the only pant that I wear. They fit well and are great for people on the go. I love that it is local and the staff at Du/er go above and beyond to make you feel seen and heard and taken care of. They ask lots of questions to make sure you are getting exactly what you want.
Friendly and super helpful staff, some of the most comfortable clothes Ive ever worn, worth checking out.

Had an awesome experience at the DUER store last week. I never had a proper jean fitting before  turns out I have been wearing the wrong size jeans! I landed on the all weather barrel pant and am so excited about them!! They are stylish enough to wear to dinner and comfy enough to wear skateboarding!!

I purchased two pairs of jeans a little over a month ago and thought they fit well when I left the store. I didn t actually wear them until about a month later and realized that I should ve gotten regular fit rather than slim. I was worried that an exchange may not be possible due to the time that had passed however, I emailed the store and they told me to bring the jeans in so they could take a look. Once they could see that I had only worn the jeans briefly they easily exchanged them for a much better fit as well as gave me the difference in the cost of the original purchase. Thank you to  Angel  at Duet. I appreciate your help and will definitely be coming back to your store as I love your products and your service.
The people working at this store are absolute gems. So helpful, patient and personable. Thanks for all your help!
Helpful staff guided me through the many options and subtle differences... and I came away happy with shorts and two pairs of pants and a free belt. Hurray!

Today I visited the store in West Hastings - for the 2nd time.  Not only are the jeans fantastic, but what makes it so appealing to return and keep buying this stuff is the amazing customer service.  Kerri is a force of nature!  This woman was not only looking after about 4 customers at the same time, (although it felt like she was just looking after me I had so much of her attention) but her knowledge of the product and what jeans will suit you is incredible!  Please give this woman a huge holiday bonus, she deserves it!

Found about DUER from a friend, and decided to get a pair of their water-repellent denim jeans. Their previous location was not convenient, so ended up ordering online, first the jeans, and later, a second pair. Recently, DUER moved to a new location on W4th and went to check it out. The store is spacious and merchandise is well organized, easy to identify (white label indicates womens clothing, black for men). Staff, friendly and helpful, one of the first questions asked is if one in familiar with the brand. If not, they will mention the different types of fabric with features that work for Vancouver weather, and the comfort when wearing it. Come to DUER and try a pair of pants, youll be impressed. Prices are quite reasonable for the quality you get. Bring your face mask.
Store is clean, well stocked  and organized. The staff are very helpful.

One must comfortable, functional and best fitted jeans I ve ever bought. I have virtually most colours in all their different fabrications. Outstanding. And equally outstanding is their new store on W 4th. Warm, attentive customer Sevice. Sasha is exceptionally helpful, knowledgeable and frank in guiding you with fits and colours. She has been amazing and makes going to their store an absolute pleasure. Can trust her to guide through their different fits and fabrics. She has great energy. Kudos DU ER!

The ordering and payment process is quick and easy.  Delivery incredibly fast.  Exchange (my fault in ordering the wrong colour) process amazing!  I sent Shirt #1 back one day and received the replacement shirt the next!  Shirts are beautiful- the cut, the fabric.  Great product, excellent customer serum.

Great service! I had called ahead to make sure they had the size and style that I wanted. I showed up, gave my name, they gave me the jeans, I tried them on and they re awesome. My BF says they are the sexiest jeans I have! Thank Duer!

If you ever feel nervous about buying trousers because you dont have the lower half of a deity then this place is wonderful. They really do a great job to make you understand the concept and their options without pressuring you to make a sale. You can swallow the perhaps above average price for the fact it wasnt made by the hands of a horrifically underpaid Bangladeshi, plus you have a one year warrantee for repairs if wear and tear is often an issue for you.

I have a pair of Duer I was  already; theyre too big for me now, but I still love wearing them as theyre perhaps the most comfortable piece of clothing I own. Great for hanging around the house, or out for a walk in the woods. But I recently wanted some casual Duer pants for business, so I visited their store here on 4th Avenue in Vancouver. I cant say enough good things about Angel, the CSR who looked after me. She was friendly, helpful and extremely knowledgeable about the styles and the slight differences in their fit. I was exceptionally impressed. Thanks Angel! My only comment was that stock in shorts and pants was a little low, I would have expected a fully stocked store, given its Duers only store in Vancouver. Later that day, I ordered some Duer shorts online, as I had a $15 first timer discount to use. Im not overly impressed with their fulfillment promises, as a delay of up to 8 days before the order is fulfilled seems out of line. Plus, shipping time on top of that. Maybe Duer will come through for me and Ill have the shorts by this weekend.

Super stoked on these pants! Everyone I talked to was so lovely and helpful. I normally hate shopping and trying things on, but here I felt so pampered - it was actually fun?! The adventure pants are comfortable, stylish, and very well-made. I can t wait to go back for another pair.

This place has the best pants! Ive been wearing DUER for a year and a half now and they are perfectly comfortable and, depending on what style you get, good for any occasion. They pay attention to details like how comfortable the pocket meterial is and how the seems sit on your body. The staff is super helpful and nice! They know their sizing well and how the material will wash and wear. A great Vancouver company!

I ve been purchasing Duer clothing for a couple years now & I have nothing but good things to say about not only the brand but it s people. Recently I had purchased a new pair of pants that unfortunately turned out to become defective after a very short period of time. The customer service / support is outstanding and class leading in my opinion. I wasn t made out to feel in any other way other than to be proud / loyal customer to the brand. Thank you Team Duer, keep on creating comfortable, practical & wonderful clothing! #AwesomeCanadianBrand

This was my first visit to the Duer store in downtown Vancouver and I was so happy that I came in. Right away I was greeted by Sean and was given the full 5-star service rundown of the different styles, fabrics, and washes. Im not typically a person to spend much time shopping, but Sean really helped me to feel sure I found the exact right pant that I wanted. I ended up walking out with two pairs and I LOVE them already. So stoked on this brand and their service I received in-store. I will be a loyal customer and fan for a long time.

Bought my first pair of pants from Dish and DUER and am already hooked. No break-in period required, the pants allow for complete freedom of movement while still being appropriate for office wear. The store layout is very laid back and inviting, it even has a swing for you to sit on while waiting for someone to try on a pair of pants in the change rooms! Staff are knowledgeable and were very helpful throughout the visit. Highly recommend!

Great staff! I was visiting Vancouver and heard about this company so I decided to check them out. Probably the greatest pair of jeans I ve owned. The pants have no stretched out and fit perfectly. The adaptive denim is really unique as well! Will definitely continue to purchase jeans from here!

Finally got to visit the physical store this weekend, as I dont like ordering online without being able to try on first. First of all, the store is really nice! Everything is laid logically and its easy to find what youre looking for. Its a roomy and attractive space. I also found the staff phenomenal. They staff member who helped me was able to explain the different styles and fabrics available, and happy to make recommendations. I tried on quite a few styles and sizes, and never felt any pressure to hurry, or to buy anything I wasnt crazy about. It was a very relaxed atmosphere and staff seemed genuinely happy to be there. I found several pairs that I was happy with. They have several different lengths, so I was able to find some pants that dont need to be hemmed (rare for me). The one pair I liked that was too long was hemmed free of charge, and mailed out to me in under a week. The quality of the fabric seems very high. I usually find that stretchy pants tend to bag out in the knees and seat throughout the day, but my Duer jeans dont. Magic!! My husband has been wearing these jeans for a couple of years, and they totally stand behind their warranty. One pair wore through in the seat after a year of service, and Duer sent him a new pair in the mail, no questions asked. These arent the cheapest jeans around, but honestly Im so done with spending money on cheap jeans that wear out in a month or dont fit well. These jeans are 100% worth the money, and Duer has phenomenal customer service!

I had been planning on coming into Duer for quite some time. I came in hoping to buy 2 pairs of jeans - I left with 1 pair of denim and 1 pair of trousers. The staff are AMAZING. everyone is kind and knowledgeable, I find 2 amazing pairs that fit great. Will definitely be back.

I had been there to buy a pair of No-sweat pants. Live lite pants were pretty comfy and I feel really good when I wear it for office duties. Staff were very professional and literally exceptional. Will helped me out with finding a right pairs in right sizes. Literally one of the best shopping experiences I ever had in my life.

I have bought three different pairs of pants from them and have loved them all. They have a lot of selection in a compact store, helpful staff, and most importantly high-quality clothing. Their prices may be more than the average pair of jeans but you will get a lot of mileage out of their jeans and pants! Super comfortable.

My friend and I visited Vancouver last year and we popped into this super adorable Canadian owned Jean company and he bought a pair. A year later (now) I end up moving to Vancouver and purchased two pairs last week. Thats how memorable the company was and the impression their store gave me. Oh, and the jeans are the most comfortable fit Ive ever found. Ever. The variety of styles and customer service cant be beat. Love yall.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Alyssa, Thanks so much for the review! Looking forward to helping you out in store again.

review_text: Great place, awesome vibes. I bought a pair of jeans here a little before Christmas. I came back today to do some patching for my other Duer pair that I bought years ago, only to find that it s been boarded up with the signs removed. I actually walked past it before realizing that it was permanently closed. Go to the one on 4th to keep supporting their business. Fantastic jeans!
Great team at Kits! Pants are comfortable. Thanks Ratif? Ratib? For helping me find a pair that fits great. Will come back again!

Locally made jeans, the fabric is very soft and stretchy, I love the pair I bought. Sign up for their email list to get a first time coupon. The store is also part factory, the staff were super helpful and knowledgeable. You have to try different sizes in the various cuts. I was 2 sizes smaller in the relaxed fit than the skinny fit.

Incredibly functional/comfortable pants with awesome customer service. Sadie was helpful and friendly in answering all my questions and explaining the history of DUER (cool local story). Adventure pants have been worn everyday since I got them. Comfortably stretchy yet fits snug, wicks sweat/water, will be buying more!

Thanks to Miguel and the rest of the staff, once again I had a really great shopping experience here. I wear only Duer Jeans every day for work and usually buy one pair every year, for the past three years. Its great that they have new styles out; this time I left with two pairs! Theyre very well suited for for our local weather here in Vancouver.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Keishin for the support and review! Happy to hear you love our pants as much as we do :)

review_text: Excellent customer service and very knowledgeable about the products. I went in to browse and all the staff were super friendly and not pushy to make a sale. I definitely will be back to buy a pair of pants!

As I have just recently bought several pairs from a sale Duer had, this is purely based on how the pants look/feel, and customer service. The event was a warehouse sale so I was only so close to getting properly fitting pants. Even so they still fit fine. Customer service was outstanding. Mathew at the flagship store is an absolute beaut! Helpful and passionate.

I am a returning customer that almost only wears Duer jeans.  During my last order, there was a mixup by Duer.  But with a quick email on my part to customer service they had everything straightened out and corrected ASAP.  A mistake happened, but you cant be upset with a company that acknowledges it and remedies is quick as they did.   Very happy with the whole experience.   I will keep buying all my casual pants from them.

My fav place for comfortable, functional yet great-looking clothing. Great for activities, work, or just hanging out. I hope that they get more selections for women, especially pants and shorts with pockets that fit a cell phone! The t-shirts are divine, made with cotton and lyocell. I chose the mens version as its more comfortable and practical versus the womens with uncomfortable cap sleeves. Thankfully, the mens sizes are slim enough for me in small or extra small. Richer colors would be great.

Functional, stunning, move easy jeans. Brayden sure knows how to make people feel at home and guide them through the process of finding the right fit, wash and style for their current jean mission. Exceptional customer service. Great atmosphere. Its clear that Dish and DU ER have a mandate to serve active people - not shopaholics! Their space is welcoming, reasonably small and full of playful elements like monkey bars and places to sit or stretch. The lighting is soft (great if mall lighting gives you headaches...) and there is zero pressure to make quick decisions and buy stuff. The staff are knowledgeable, supportive and make every effort to help you find precisely what you need. The jeans are durable, attractive and comfortable ... so much so that I believe I have accidentally entered into a monogamous relationship with this denim provider.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your feedback Marisa! We have something for you to say thanks. Shoot us a note at contactus@dishandduer.com.

review_text: DUER, you had me at gussets, stitched down inseams, and real pockets. Local, sustainable,  great styling and fit   I m yours for good. Friendly staff; good shopping experience, featuring a Landyachtz test bike in the store just so you can see how the jeans perform. Love it.

I bought five pair of pants (two pairs two years ago, still look like brand new) and will buy more. Despite the fact that I am almost 60 years old, the pants fit me perfectly, make me look slimmer, no hanging backside, the crotch looks normal and no need to mention the feeling that I have when wearing them: soft, comfortable, no sweating, stretchable, no tightness around testicles, absolutely fabulous. I have to wear formal clothing at work but some of these pant, although informal style, can pass as formal combined with the suit jacket. After sitting for 8 hours at work, no sweating in the crotch area. Very satisfied. Going these days to check what they have new, have not been there for 6 months.

I am very pleased with the service I received at the Vancouver location. After placing an order online that did not meet my expectations, I went in to the store to discuss my concerns. Although the product should not have been eligible for return, the staff (and what I assume was the manager) listened to my issue with the purchase, and did the right thing by offering an immediate return. Its often easy to stick to a policy, but by taking the time to listen and react to this one off situation, they have earned my continued loyalty and my recommendations going forward.

Ive been following DUER on Instagram for a while and finally needed some new jeans, so checked them out today. I had such great service from Angel who was very attentive, and listened (I dont like shopping so always appreciate thoughtful opinions and suggestions). review_text: Ive discovered the brand at the Whistler Bike Conference in Whistler and took a year to come down check it out. Looking for me it was their warehouse sale and everything was half price or more! Got 3 set of pants, and I would go back for 3 more even at full price. Most comfy casual clean looking pants ever!

Incredibly comfortable, great service, though not terribly durable. Mine started to wear through in the crotch after about five months of almost daily use. I have fairly large thighs (too many squats!) so this isnt terribly uncommon; I went through two pairs of Levis in about a year before the Duer jeans. What was uncommon is they offered to replace them on the spot with zero hassle. I was on the fence about Duer when I went in. Theyre by far the most comfortable jeans Ive ever worn, but I was concerned about the durability. If they didnt offer to refund/replace the jeans after tearing in such a short period I would have walked away from the brand, but the service I received really stood out. I was so impressed I ended up buying a couple extra pairs while I was in there :D. If youre in the market for some jeans I strongly suggest you give Duer a try, theyre unbelievably comfortable, the staff are great, and they really stand behind their product.

The Winners & Homesence combination store is the only way to go if you plan on spending money. I cant imagine walking out of this combination store without something I needed. If you like something, but you dont like making impulsive shopping decisions, my suggestion is to go and have a coffee or take a little breather outside. Make the decision whether you ARE or NOT going to buy after you remove yourself from all the stimulation of all the stuff set up in such a way that you cant help but desire it ...but just make sure that you dont remove yourself for too long. Because if you go home and think about it and come to decide, after a good nights sleep, that you absolutely MUST have it...guess what its no longer going to be there. It will be GONE. This has happened to me so many times!! This is how I used to make purchases. Any item that I loved when I was in the store and was still thinking about the next day, would be something I believed worth buying. There is such a range of stylish on-trend clothes, accessories, make-up, furniture, decor etc from sandals & giant wall clocks to doggie dresses & mens cologne that you will find what you forgot you needed without much effort at all and at decent prices. Check out my pretty towels and the cutest ever portable doggy bed.

review_text: Great selection, wasnt busy, and staff said hello shortly after we entered. Have shopped here 1/2 a doz times over the last couple years, and I will go back again.

Marks Work Wearhouse (And why you should shop there!) About a year ago I was diagnosed with Type 2 Diabetes. I had just purchased 4 mens dress shirts, size XXL relaxed fit. I wore one shirt, and the remaining 3 shirts sat in the drawer unopened. I have spent the last 10+ months eating healthy (Keto Lifestyle) and exercising daily. I routinely walk a minimum of 8 kilometers per day, and up to 20 - 30 kilometers on Saturdays and Sundays . . . rain, snow, or shine. I have recently got back on my road bike as well. As a result, my body size has reduced dramatically. I now wear a mens L or XL, slim fit and my waist is now 32.5 (down from 44) I contacted Marks Work Wearhouse in-store to find out if I could exchange the unopened shirts I purchased online. Sadly the store clerk couldnt help me, but she was very nice and apologized. I contacted Marks Work Wearhouse online and within a couple of weeks, smaller sized shirts have arrived on my doorstep. I was told by Marks Work Wearhouse to donate the unopened XXL shirts to charity. The Lady from Marks also congratulated me on my accomplishment. This is a great example of a community oriented company going above and beyond the call. At least for me, they have a satisfied customer for life. This is why I will always shop at Marks Work Wearhouse.

We were beyond excited when his hard work paid off and he successfully found the One and Only one left in their store or any of the locations around!!! There were people in the store and the cash register staff were able to move people quickly so the wait time was about 30seconds.  The emailed me the receipt and it was correct. I spent just over $100 and saved $20 from the sale prices.

I had a great experience shopping at this location. Chris was very helpful and went above and beyond for helping me out and finding what I needed. I was looking for a shoe size that was not availible on the sales floor and asked if they had any out back in the storage. After finding out they did not have it at their store, he looked at the other North Vancouver location for me and called them to confirm so he could save me the drive. After finding out that they were out as well (Even though the system showed that they had 1)  Chris placed an order for me where it was shipped to my house 2 days after the purchus date. Great customer service Chris, I appriciate it and will be back at this store again. Thank you Marks Marine Drive and Chris for your outstanding customer service! Al
